.TH "shutdown_device" 9 "shutdown_device" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
shutdown_device \- shut down a device
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" shutdown_device
.BI "(struct hfi1_devdata *dd "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dd" 12
the hfi1_ib device
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This is called to make the device quiet when we are about to
unload the driver, and also when the device is administratively
disabled.   It does not free any data structures.
Everything it does has to be setup again by hfi1_init(dd, 1)
